description:
&lt;p&gt;There is an opportunity to join Health Innovation Manchester on a fixed term or secondment basis as a Senior Programme Development Lead- Band 8a in the Patient Safety Collaborative (PSC) programme. This role would suit an internal or external candidate who wishes to develop more insight into the National Patient Safety Programme work that Health Innovation Manchester (HInM) undertakes within the Greater Manchester and Eastern Cheshire (GMEC) area- specifically within the MatNeo and Deterioration workstreams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Programme Development Lead role is responsible for designing and implementing large-scale improvement programmes across Greater Manchester. The post holder will have proven knowledge of quality improvement, innovation and implementation methods, having demonstrated a track record in delivery. You will have experience at developing innovative and new ideas, solutions and strategies for improving patient care, safety and clinical outcomes. You will have a track record of engaging with multi-professional teams ideally across organisational boundaries and knowledge of working in both primary, acute care and private sectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role would offer a great opportunity for someone to gain experience, knowledge and skills of working at a more senior level within HInM Within our wider HInM organisation we also support innovation into healthcare settings from research undertaken in our 4 main universities. Our work is fast paced, innovative and increasingly focussed on potential digital solutions for healthcare system needs; with overt support in the PSC team for the GMEC system around teaching and embedding quality improvement approaches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameWendy StobbsJob titleSenior Programme Development LeadEmail addresswendy.stobbs@healthinnovationmanchester.comAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
